UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='Resting in Pieces', `LogDescription`='Bring Alaric\'s Head to his grave.', `QuestDescription`='You don\'t look like a rot hide.  Good.  I had lost hope...$B$BMy name is Alaric, and I was once Thule\'s head servant and bodyguard.  He used his magic to \"protect\" me from the Plague of Undeath, but instead his spell gave me an unlife from which I cannot escape.  And after creating the cursed rot hide gnolls, Thule beheaded me... and gave my head to the gnolls as a plaything!$B$BPlease, take me to my body.  I believe the gnolls buried it here in Fenris Keep, near the stable, in an unmarked grave.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=460 AND `locale`='deDE');
UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='Delivery to Silverpine Forest', `LogDescription`='Take Apothecary Holland\'s findings to Apothecary Renferrel in Silverpine Forest.', `QuestDescription`='Time is a luxury that is not afforded to those of us under the employ of Lady Sylvanas.  Surely you know this by now.$b$bAs a member of the Royal Apothecary Society it is my duty to share my knowledge with my colleagues so that our collective efforts might one day provide The Dark Lady with the New Plague she so badly desires.$b$bTake these findings to Apothecary Renferrel who is stationed at The Sepulcher in Silverpine Forest.  Follow the roads to the south from Brill.  From the Undercity go southwest.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=445 AND `locale`='deDE');
UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='A Putrid Task', `LogDescription`='Bring 7 Putrid Claws to Deathguard Dillinger in Brill.', `QuestDescription`='Scourge have trickled into Tirisfal Glades and have infested the area west of Brill, near the old bridge.$B$BGo there and beat back the rotting dead and ravaged corpses you find.  Scatter their bones and bring back their putrid claws, and the Deathguards will reward you.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=404 AND `locale`='deDE');
UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='The Damned', `LogDescription`='Obtain 4 Scavenger Paws and 4 Duskbat Wings.', `QuestDescription`='My duties include tending to our wounded warriors, tailoring armor and clothes, and assisting Shadow Priest Sarvis with whatever else he might need.$b$bFrom the look of it, you\'ll be enlisted in his service also... hunting the Mindless Ones, if I know his mind. Well, if you\'d like to stay in one piece--and I\'ve no doubt you do--perhaps I can help. I\'m running out of paws and wings, and if you bring me some, I\'ll find some armor for you. You\'ll find a good number of wolves and bats to the south.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=376 AND `locale`='deDE');
UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='A New Plague', `LogDescription`='Apothecary Johaan of the town of Brill needs 5 Vile Fin Scales from Murlocs in Tirisfal Glades.', `QuestDescription`='While you were collecting samples for me, my experiments led me to realize that more reagents will be required for this new disease to spread properly. Poisoning some hapless victim is child\'s play. Plaguing an entire world proves to be a bit more complicated.$b$bI will need 5 Vile Fin Scales from Murlocs in the vicinity.  You will find the creatures along the coast to the north or to the west.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=368 AND `locale`='deDE');
UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='The Mindless Ones', `LogDescription`='Kill 5 Mindless Zombies and 5 Wretched Ghouls.', `QuestDescription`='Since the first Forsaken crawled out of his tomb, we have been at war with the Lich King\'s army of the Scourge: necromantically raised armies of the undead, foul beasts of the north, and tormented spectres.$b$bThe Lich King no longer sits the Frozen Throne, but the northern part of the village remains overrun with his slaves.  Destroy them, show them no mercy, our former brothers and sisters as they might be.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=364 AND `locale`='deDE');
UPDATE `quest_template_locale` SET `LogTitle`='Rear Guard Patrol', `LogDescription`='Kill 8 Bleeding Horrors and 8 Wandering Spirits.', `QuestDescription`='Here at the Bulwark, we must be on constant alert to protect Tirisfal from Scourge incursions.  Even so, sometimes the Scourge will slip past us.$B$BOur success at the Bulwark depends on a one-front battle - we cannot allow an attack from the rear, nor can we allow our supply line to be cut.$B$BPatrol west and slay any Scourge you find.  Spend particular effort at the Balnir Farmstead.  It has become a haven for interloping Scourge.', `VerifiedBuild`=29981 WHERE (`ID`=356 AND `locale`='deDE');
